# Project Overview
Frontend application integrating AI features for the FlyRank capstone.

# Tech Stack
- UI Framework: React 
- Syntax: ES6+ JavaScript, strictly using Functional Components and Hooks
- Environment: Node.js (LTS)

# AI Engineering Conventions
- Write clean, modular, and reusable components.
- Avoid deprecated React patterns (no class components).
- Prioritize clear error handling, especially when interfacing with AI endpoints or APIs.
- Keep terminal commands limited to npm/git operations.
- Always follow Conventional Commits formatting for git history.
- Always use proper semantic HTML tags and ARIA attributes for form accessibility.
- All form components must evaluate local validation state and disable submission buttons if constraints are not met.
- Include a state for inputs to prevent validation errors from displaying before the user interacts with the field.